This paper discusses the field of semantic parsing, which involves converting natural language utterances to logical forms that can be executed on a knowledge base. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
